<title>SINGAPORE: Goldtron sells Measurex shares.</title>
<headline>Goldtron sells Measurex shares.</headline>
<dateline>SINGAPORE 1997-05-29</dateline>
<text>
<p>Electronics firm Goldtron Ltd said on Thursday it had sold a total of eight million Measurex Corporation Bhd (MCB) shares for about Singapore $33.2 million.</p>
<p>Goldtron said in a statement proceeds from the sale, together with the S$44.9 million received from the initial public offer of MCB, would be used to repay bank borrowings and for working capital.</p>
<p>After the sale, Goldtron still holds the balance of 7.96 million shares or 19.95 percent of MCB, which is listed on the second board of the Kuala Lumpur Stock Exchange.</p>
<p>Goldtron said MCB had ceased to be an associated company after the sale.</p>
<p>- Singapore Newsroom 65-8703080</p>
